==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[Vulcan]]'': The God of fire.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/vɒlkeɪnəʊ/}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|pl2=volcanoes}}

#A [[mountain]] that contains a [[magma]] chamber attached to the [[mantle]] of the [[planet]] or [[moon]] and which periodically [[erupt]]s forth, usually explosively, with [[lava]] and volcanic [[gas]]es.

